ATTACHMENT A Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 Harts Mill Solar, LLC Reactive Power Compensation
HARTS MILL SOLAR, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Harts Mill Solar, LLC ("Harts Mill") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Harts Mill generating facility ("Harts Mill Facility").
The Harts Mill Facility is a solar generating facility located in Edgecombe County, North Carolina. The Harts Mill Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Virginia Electric and Power Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Harts Mill's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Harts Mill Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Harts Mill's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Harts Mill shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $1,210,086.33 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $100,840.53
